,Recommended,324190,20356385,"Posted: 6 January, 2016",all,Deadreign4,"I bought this game recently, as you can see only played it for a few of hours, so this isn't an in depth review, just my first impressions. This will be very long winded so read another review if you do not have the patience for long reviews! This game is in very early access, so i am impressed with how far it has got already. I have already created a few simple spells and though there is not much to it yet, there is enough to explore and enough content to have a few hours of entertainment with no trouble. The forums are very helpful, and if you are new to code, you can get spells from them to help you learn how to create your own. From what i have seen, the developers are very active, update the game often, and the development is very user-feedback centered, meaning all of your favourite features that you request have a good chance of being implemented. Anybody buying this game should definitely make an account on the forums where they are very helpful and there is no trash talking or any innapropriate comments whatsoever. But back to the game. It is fairly impressive graphics wise, and the physics do not take a supercomputer to run, which is good, as my computer is not great. In case anybody is interested i will put these at the bottom so that you can get an idea of how yours will run. The possibilities of what you can do with these spells is not literally endless, like the description says, but there is more than i care to discover. It would take thousands of hours of tinkering with JS or the blocks to discover them all and new code is being added all the time. I would highly recommend this to anyone who has ever dreamed of being a wizard or liked skyrims spells but didnt like the lack of invention with the spells. You do not need any history of coding to learn this, especially with the forums. Thanks for reading this review, however long winded and hope to see you on the forums sharing spells